relation.text: Wednesday Clarges Street Br in my own Room work 'd
had told my our Uncle William & Cousin Chs : Greville yesterday
went to bed at 1 oClock . August 19
Thursday Got up early dreſs at ½ past 7 for ye . day A : M : but poorly gave
had seen his Brother Sir William Yesterday
went to bed . No letter from D——shire 20 th . August 1784
Thursday -- at 8 had my Hair dreſs 'd for ye . day -- A Maria so well this Morng . that she got up
wd . if poſsible call on Mrs. Delany today
August -- 84 Breakfast in my own Room dreſsd at 9 for ye . day -- A M . better . ye . Watchmaker came
gave it to with Lady S—— letters to her Servt . for this nights
talk 'd of my Uncle William -- Lord S—— related ye . conversation that had paſs 'd between their Majesties & him on Thursday
aſsured her that was by no means ye . Case but he had been so happy 22 years
shared in my concern abt . ye . loſs of ye . Packet of ye . 10 th . Sunday 22 August 1784
s Birth day -- little Charles , who is to day was 3 Years
Thursday the Prince of Wales told
begun a letter to my D—— Monday
a few days at her villa & also desired
went to our Rooms at ½ past 11 -- Tuesday 24 August
is quoted at length in Anson & Anson ( 1925
had seen my Uncle F : yesterday
a few days into to Nottinghamshire & that he wd
found her & little Henry very well & not ye . worse for ye . Company & fatigue of Yesterday
return 'd from Margate to day . Thursday
Thursday Br with A. M . sat
went to bed ½ past 11 Friday
set out for Worcester wch . wd . be on Tuesday
led us on till 12 oClock Saturday
arrived in Town frm . Scotland . Yesterday
will stay only a few days
aſsured me he had been perfectly happy since his marriage with Miſs Clavering Lady Napier . wch . is now
August 1784 As I had not been well in ye . Night I did not get up
told me that not on I was not now
was married to Miſs S. Thynne yesterday
Tuesday -- that ye . sooner I came
wanted me to be with them her from next Week
come for two or three days
s at Thames Ditton -- to each a few days
hoped to be with her in ten Days
read me some more of her friends letters Monday
went to Windsor with Mr. Greville & yesterday
was nearly gone . & wd . be perfectly so in a day or two
dined at Courteenhall a few days ago
said of abt . her in my letter of Yesterday
related to me some private conversation he had wth . ye . King yesterday
let off by some person at ye . End of our Street -- there are dozens of them every night . Septr . 3 d . 1784
told me he had been absent 5 Weeks
related some curious Anecdotes of ye . & an entertaining quarrel he had a day or two ago
last week -- he was so long closetted wth . their M 's
s at Richmond Park for 2 or 3 days
went to our Rooms soon after 11 Saturday
yesterday he had an Audience of ye . King & ask
regain 'd composure & c & c & c & c & c the Heart is now
had hoped to have me for a long time
her support but that a Guinea a Year
took his last farewell after mutual wishes that only 3 or 4 Years
1784 Sent Miſs C at 7 o'Clock wth . a Note & a Brace of ye . Partridges to Lady Herries at Chelsea . At ½ past 8 met
told me that he had now
went to bed abt . 11 oClock An extreme hot day Saturday
went to my Room before 12 . Sunday
Months nothing more I took out
went to bed soon after 1 2 1 -- Tuesday
'd b a n hour before dinner -- this day
wrote letters to A M & Mrs. J—— . Thursday
Friday 17 th .. Septr .. Harwood -- Recd . letter from my Mrs. J dated frm- Elvaston 11 th Sepr Wm . Benn wrote
took Mrs. Jackson with her -- this day
1784 Lady Wake & Mr .. Lane & Mr . -- dined
1784 Septr . Harwood Miſs Morel & Mary went
1784 Miſs Gunning & Betty return 'd from Town -- brought
dated 1 5 4 th -- & one from Master Franklin . Thursday

March was as foll ows Master Murray & Mr. Nicholson & Lady S in her Phaeton & 4 & 2 Servts . George myself -- little Chl upon Lord Stormont lap & Henry upon Mrs. Bridges 's

Winter for their Health -- the 3 Miſs M——ys
days Post -- ye . Ducheſs Dr. of Portland had frank 'd ye . Covers -- Lady Wake came

1784 . Wandworth Hill Lady Stormont & I took
1784 Wandworth Hill Mr. Johnson & I went

will be in London this Winter
Sion Ho use at present Thursday

'd me some Drawer of fine Foſsils Minerals Monday
'd in ye . usual delightful & agreeable Manner . Tuesday
